The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 February is 36,657 (4,242.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 January, there were 2,365 new confirmed cases (273.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 January, there were 3,294 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 28% (929 fewer cases).
